 '(110 120 130 140 150
   160 170 180 190 200))

(setq sorted-lengths
      '(85 86 110 116 122 129 154 176 179 200 265 300 300))

(defuns-per-range sorted-lengths top-of-ranges)
@end group
@end smallexample

@need 800
@noindent
The list returned looks like this:

@smallexample
(2 2 2 0 0 1 0 2 0 0 4)
@end smallexample

@noindent
